 POST: The biggest impact of AI will be in education and no one is talking about it.

Bloom’s two sigma problem explains that students who receive 1-on-1 instruction perform 98% better than the average control classroom student.

We’ve known for 50 years how to fix education, we just haven’t had the resources to give every student a teacher.

Now they have one that works 24/7, can teach everything from Spanish to physics to the fall of the roman empire.

And it fits in the palm of their hand.

The Cambrian explosion of knowledge driven by curiosity among children begins now, if we encourage it and don’t demonize it.
